# Writing generic classes and methods

## Generic class — one def, any type

```java
public class Box<T> {
    private T value;
    public T get() { return value; }
}
Box<Double> p = new Box<>(3.14);   // <> infers the type
```

## Generic method — own type param before the return type

```java
public static <T> T firstOrNull(List<T> list) { ... }
Util.firstOrNull(List.of(1, 2, 3));   // T = Integer
```
